CBP uses a variety of techniques to assure that global tourism remains safe and strong. Travelers coming from the ports border with Canada or Mexico using different entry types such as Personal Vehicle, Bus, Trains, Trucks, Pedestrians and many more. Getting quick insight about average number of people entering to united states by using different ports has significant meaning to all kind of travel related business and better decision making to provide best customer service and further planning of those ports.
